messages.msg: Welcome to our site! If you are looking for prayer or someone to chat with, reply to this message or email us at prayer@fightlust.com

I pray that God would deliver me from all worldliness and I pray that he would grant me deliverance from the works of the enemy I pray that he would grant me repentance for all the ways that I have opposed the word of God i pray that he would grant me repentance and salvation for all the ways I allowed the devil to ensnare me in doing his will I want to live holy be a faithful husband and true holy man of God in my home

Thank you for sharing your heartfelt prayer. It's wonderful to hear your desire for deliverance and holiness. If you'd like, I can guide you through some prayers and scriptures that can support you in this journey. Would you like to receive specific prayers or resources?
Yes

Great! Here are some prayers and scriptures that can help you in your journey towards deliverance and holiness:

1. **Prayer for Deliverance**: 
   "Heavenly Father, I come before you seeking deliverance from all worldliness and the works of the enemy. Please grant me repentance for the ways I have opposed your word. Help me to turn away from sin and to live a life that is pleasing to you. In Jesus' name, Amen."

2. **Scripture for Strength**: 
   - **James 4:7**: "Submit yourselves, then, to God. Resist the devil, and he will flee from you."
   - **1 Corinthians 10:13**: "No temptation has overtaken you except what is common to mankind. And God is faithful; he will not let you be tempted beyond what you can bear."

3. **Prayer for Holiness**: 
   "Lord, I desire to live a holy life and to be a faithful husband. Help me to be a true man of God in my home. Fill me with your Spirit and guide my actions and thoughts. In Jesus' name, Amen."

If you need more specific resources or support, feel free to let me know!

I want to be a true man of God in the church as well I pray that God would grant me repentance for opposing his word and encouraging others and leading others to do so I repent of all sexual sin that I have been involved with I pray that God would lead me back into his truth from over the years and to not walk in and live in error from this day forward I pray that he would enable me to run from the very appearance of evil and to no longer be ensnared in the work of the enemy

Welcome! It's wonderful to hear your heartfelt desire for repentance and to live a life aligned with God's truth. We're here to support you in your journey. Would you like to share a specific prayer request, or would you like guidance on scriptures that can help you in this process?
Prayer and scripture

Absolutely! Here are some scriptures and prayers that can guide you in your journey towards repentance and living a holy life:

1. **Philippians 4:6** - "Be anxious for nothing, but in everything by prayer and supplication, with thanksgiving, let your requests be made known to God." This verse encourages you to bring your requests to God in prayer.

2. **Matthew 6:9-13** - The Lord's Prayer provides a framework for how to pray. It emphasizes seeking God's will and asking for forgiveness.

3. **Ephesians 6:18** - "Praying at all times in the Spirit, with all prayer and supplication." This reminds you to stay alert and persistent in prayer.

4. **Psalm 100:4-5** - "Enter his gates with thanksgiving, and his courts with praise! Give thanks to him; bless his name!" This encourages you to approach God with a heart of gratitude.

**Prayer for Repentance:**
"Dear Heavenly Father, I come before You with a humble heart, seeking Your forgiveness for my sins. I repent of all sexual sin and ask for Your grace to lead me back to Your truth. Help me to run from the appearance of evil and to stand firm against the enemy's work in my life. Fill me with Your Spirit and guide me in Your ways. In Jesus' name, I pray. Amen."

If you need more specific prayers or guidance, feel free to ask!

That would be nice I want and need God's strength to walk away from this sinful lifestyle and the ensnarement of the enemy I want the spirit of truth to open my eyes to God's truth and for God to guide me into his truth and deliverance from the ensnarement and trap of the enemy

It's wonderful to hear your desire for God's strength and guidance. Let's pray together for your journey towards deliverance and truth.

Heavenly Father, we come before you today, seeking your strength and guidance. We ask that you open our eyes to your truth and lead us away from the snares of the enemy. Help us to walk in your ways and to resist temptation. We trust in your promise that when we submit to you, the enemy will flee. Fill us with your Holy Spirit and empower us to live a life that honors you. In Jesus' name, we pray. Amen.

If you would like specific scriptures or further prayers to support you, just let me know!
All of that helps I appreciate it

You're very welcome! I'm glad to hear that it helps. Remember, we're here to support you on your journey. If you need more prayers, scriptures, or just someone to talk to, feel free to reach out anytime. How else can I assist you today?
Prayers and scriptures are helpful I appreciate it don't mean to be a bother

You're not a bother at all! It's my pleasure to help you. Here are some scriptures and prayers that can support you in your journey:

**Scriptures:**
1. **Philippians 4:6-7**: "Do not be anxious about anything, but in everything by prayer and supplication with thanksgiving let your requests be made known to God. And the peace of God, which surpasses all understanding, will guard your hearts and your minds in Christ Jesus."
2. **Ephesians 6:18**: "Praying at all times in the Spirit, with all prayer and supplication. To that end, keep alert with all perseverance, making supplication for all the saints."
3. **Matthew 7:7**: "Ask, and it will be given to you; seek, and you will find; knock, and it will be opened to you."

**Prayer for Strength and Guidance:**
"Lord, I ask for your strength to resist temptation and to walk in your truth. Help me to seek you in all things and to trust in your guidance. May your Spirit lead me away from the traps of the enemy and into your light. Amen."

If you need more specific prayers or scriptures, just let me know!
Anything that you have I appreciate it mainly I want deliverance and repentance from the spirit of error and to be released from the love of the world and worldly living

It's wonderful that you're seeking deliverance and repentance. Here’s a prayer that may resonate with your desire for freedom from the spirit of error and worldly living:

**Deliverance Prayer:**
"Father, in the name of Jesus Christ, I come before you seeking deliverance from the spirit of error and the love of the world. I ask that you cleanse my heart and mind, helping me to turn away from worldly desires and to focus on your truth. Fill me with your Holy Spirit and guide me in living a life that is pleasing to you. I surrender my will to you and ask for your strength to resist temptation. Thank you for your grace and mercy. Amen."

Additionally, here are some scriptures that can encourage you in this journey:

1. **1 John 2:15-17**: "Do not love the world or the things in the world. If anyone loves the world, the love of the Father is not in him. For all that is in the world—the desires of the flesh and the desires of the eyes and pride of life—is not from the Father but is from the world. And the world is passing away along with its desires, but whoever does the will of God abides forever."
   
2. **Romans 12:2**: "Do not be conformed to this world, but be transformed by the renewal of your mind, that by testing you may discern what is the will of God, what is good and acceptable and perfect."

If you need further support or specific resources, feel free to ask!
Thanks for everything it just seems like being released from the enemies camp and worldliness is hard

I understand that it can feel challenging to break free from the enemy's camp and worldly influences. Remember, you're not alone in this struggle. It's important to lean on God's strength and guidance during these times. 

Feeling overwhelmed is common, but God’s grace is sufficient for you. Here’s a reminder: 

**2 Corinthians 12:9**: "But he said to me, 'My grace is sufficient for you, for my power is made perfect in weakness.' Therefore I will boast all the more gladly of my weaknesses, so that the power of Christ may rest upon me."

If you ever feel discouraged, reach out for support, whether through prayer or connecting with others who understand your journey. We're here to help you find the strength and resources you need. Would you like to share a specific prayer request or talk more about what you're experiencing?
No I appreciate everything

You're very welcome! I'm glad to hear that. If you ever need support, guidance, or someone to talk to, don't hesitate to reach out. Remember, we're here for you on your journey towards healing. Take care, and may you find peace and strength in your faith!
